USER RESEARCH
================================================================================

TOP 5 PAIN POINTS
-----------------
1. Skill barrier — readers want floral nails but assume they require salon-level
   technique; they need permission to try simpler versions (tulip accent, daisy
   dot) and clear skill-level signals per design.

2. Longevity anxiety — especially for textured/3D and pressed flower designs;
   readers worry 3D blooms will snag or lift; they want reassurance on wear time
   (pressed flowers: 2–3 weeks under hard gel; 3D gel: salon-applied can last
   similar to a full gel set).

3. Design decision paralysis — so many floral sub-types (cherry blossom, daisy,
   3D rose, pressed, wildflower, abstract) that readers don't know which suits
   their nail shape, skill level, or occasion. They need a decision framework.

4. Colour overwhelm — florals require coordinating base + petal + accent colours;
   readers want to know what colour combos are actually working in 2026 without
   trial and error (sage green + white daisy, butter yellow + white bloom, nude +
   blush cherry blossom are the validated combos).

5. "Is this worth the salon price?" — 3D sculptural florals run £80–£120 / $80–$120
   per set; readers want to know what justifies the cost vs what they can DIY
   convincingly in 20–30 minutes at home.

USER SENTIMENT:
  Aspirational and excited — florals are the spring look readers most want to try,
  but skill anxiety and choice overload create hesitation before booking or buying.

