H2 STRUCTURE (8 H2s recommended — maps to design families + decision layers):
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
H2 1: Why Spring 2026 Florals Feel Different This Year
  → Editorial hook: dimensional vs flat, minimalist placement, the 2026 shift.
  Weave in: spring-nail-ideas (link) naturally here as broader context.

H2 2: Cherry Blossom Nails — The Minimalist Signature Look
  → The season's most searched sub-type. Single cluster on accent nail, nude/milky
  base, soft pink + white. Works on any length. Beginner-achievable.
  IMAGE: 1 hero shot of cherry blossom set — almond or oval, milky base.

H2 3: Micro Daisy Nails and Daisy French Tips
  → High-save content on TikTok. Covers two executions: scattered micros (size 000
  brush / dotting tool) and daisy French tips (sage green or butter yellow tips +
  white daisy details). Beginner–intermediate.
  LINK: spring-french-tip-nails — "for more French tip variations, see our guide"
  IMAGE: 1 close-up of daisy French tip in sage + white.

H2 4: 3D Sculpted Flower Nails — The Salon Statement
  → Roses, peonies, ranunculus. Builder gel vs acrylic. Pricing context ($80–$120,
  90–120 min). Ring finger placement. The viral TikTok category (4.2M plays for
  sculpted flower tutorials). Salon-recommended; brief note on builder gel for
  adventurous home users.
  IMAGE: 1 shot of 3D rose / peony on almond nail, nude base.

H2 5: Pressed Flower Nails — Real Botanicals Under Gel
  → Pinterest saves up 200%+ YoY. Violets, baby's breath, forget-me-nots
  encapsulated under hard gel. Intermediate technique. Longevity: 2–3 weeks.
  Key care note: flowers must be fully dried before application (browning risk).
  IMAGE: 1 image of pressed flower set — translucent, oval or short coffin.

H2 6: Wildflower Meadow Nails and Abstract Florals
  → Maximalist end of the spectrum. Scattered botanicals on soft white/pale green
  base. Also covers abstract / watercolour florals (colour movement over literal
  shapes). Intermediate–advanced but achievable with stickers for beginners.
  IMAGE: 1 image of wildflower meadow set showing intentional scatter.

H2 7: Which Nail Shape Works Best for Spring Florals?
  → Data-backed shape section: almond + oval = most versatile (enough surface,
  elegant proportion); coffin for 3D and maximalist; short squoval for micro florals
  and pressed. Reinforces why design choice links to shape.
  LINK: almond-spring-nails — "almond is the season's top shape"

H2 8: The 2026 Floral Colour Palette (and How to Build Your Own Combo)
  → Consolidates colour data: butter yellow + white / sage green + white daisy /
  nude + blush cherry blossom / milky white + any petal / lavender + micro bloom.
  Glossy finish = most popular (glazed topcoat, high-shine gel). Matte works for
  wildflower maximalist. Jelly/sheer base = pressed flower and micro floral.
  LINK: spring-nail-art-at-home — "for step-by-step how-tos on DIY floral designs"

STRUCTURE REASONING:
  Opens with editorial framing (why 2026 is different) to hook engaged readers, then
